{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011HCLR6d5hRfcJvECQTcjRA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# VCS\n     2→.git/\n     3→\n     4→# Maven\n     5→.mvn/\n     6→**/.mvn/\n     7→mvnw\n     8→mvnw.cmd\n     9→**/mvnw\n    10→**/mvnw.cmd\n    11→target/\n    12→**/target/\n    13→pom.xml.tag\n    14→pom.xml.releaseBackup\n    15→pom.xml.versionsBackup\n    16→pom.xml.next\n    17→release.properties\n    18→dependency-reduced-pom.xml\n    19→buildNumber.properties\n    20→\n    21→# IDE / Editor\n    22→.vscode/\n    23→**/.vscode/\n    24→.zed/\n    25→**/.zed/\n    26→.idea/\n    27→**/.idea/\n    28→*.iml\n    29→*.ipr\n    30→*.iws\n    31→\n    32→# OS\n    33→.DS_Store\n    34→**/.DS_Store\n    35→Thumbs.db\n    36→ehthumbs.db\n    37→\n    38→# Logs / temp\n    39→*.log\n    40→*.tmp\n    41→*.temp\n    42→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"676aef34-a104-4ccc-a6b8-6d02041be5cc","uuid":"8d3a187f-ee8f-411d-b3f3-fcdbe5208206"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_013gpg8BKSQWcVKnrvJKHvfW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me update the todo list and begin the migration.\n\n**Analysis Summary:**\n- Spring Boot 3.3.7 with JoinFaces (PrimeFaces JSF integration)\n- Spring Data JPA repositories\n- H2 in-memory database\n- JSF/PrimeFaces web layer with XHTML templates\n- 7 entities, 5 repositories, 2 services, 1 managed bean\n\nThe migration strategy for Quarkus:\n1. Replace Spring Data JPA with Quarkus Hibernate ORM + Panache repositories\n2. Replace JoinFaces/PrimeFaces with Quarkus MyFaces extension\n3. Replace `@Service`/`@Component` with CDI `@ApplicationScoped`/`@Dependent`\n4. Replace `@Autowired` with `@Inject`\n5. Replace `@EventListener(ApplicationReadyEvent)` with Quarkus `@Observes StartupEvent`\n6. Add REST endpoint for smoke tests\n7. Convert `application.properties` to Quarkus format"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6902,"cache_read_input_tokens":41914,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6902,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":769},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"676aef34-a104-4ccc-a6b8-6d02041be5cc","uuid":"36caee82-8c9b-42f8-8197-81763470ad10"}
